        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 19 at 11:58PM CDT by NWS Goodland KS</headline>
        <description>At 1158 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms 4 miles north of Park, or 5 miles northeast of
Grainfield, moving east at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

This storm will remain over mainly rural areas of southern Sheridan,
northeastern Gove and southwestern Graham Counties, including the
following locations... Penokee, Saint Peter, and Studley.

This includes Interstate 70 in Kansas between mile markers 87 and
113.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Frequent cloud to ground lightning is occurring with this storm.
Lightning can strike 10 miles away from a thunderstorm. Seek a safe
shelter inside a building or vehicle.</instruction>
